OL,3,C'Costly mistake' that some
OL,4,Cholidaymakers are making when
OL,5,Ctravelling abroad
OL,7,FThe most common expenses included
OL,8,Ftipping, taxi fares and shopping at
OL,9,Flocal or independent retailers,
OL,10,Faccording to the research.
OL,12,FPrepaid and specialist travel cards
OL,13,Fcan make it easier to rely less on
OL,14,Fphysical cash while travelling
OL,15,Foverseas.
OL,17,FBut those suddenly needing that cash
OL,18,Fcould end up paying extra costs, the
OL,19,Fsurvey carried out by Opinium, among
OL,20,F2,000 people across the UK who have
OL,21,Ftravelled abroad, indicates.
