OL,5,Ctravelling abroad
OL,7,FThe website said that stepping outside
OL,8,Fmajor cities can also present
OL,9,Fchallenges, as rural and remote areas
OL,10,Fin some countries could be less likely
OL,11,Fto accept cards.
OL,13,FAmelia Murray, a money expert at Be
OL,14,FClever With Your Cash, said: "There's
OL,15,Fstill a blind spot when it comes to
OL,16,Fcash. Many people assume that having a
OL,17,Ffee-free card is enough, but that can
OL,18,Fbe a false economy if you end up using
OL,19,Fan ATM abroad that charges or get
OL,20,Fstung by poor exchange rates.
